paper_abstract: A chemical ant colony algorithm (CACA) with supramolecular coefficient gamma was put forward. It has successfully solved the multivariate calibration issue of the supramolecule analysis system, and realized the pure spectra fitting and the simultaneous determination of the calix[n]arenas(n=4, 6, 8) in a multicomponent supramolecular system. The analyzing errors for calix[4, 6, 8]arenas through Chemical Ant Colony Algorithm with supramolecular coefficient gamma are within +/- 3.75%. The errors by CACA are within +/- 7.50%. The former obviously excels the latter. Copyright (C) 2008 John Wiley & Sons, Ltd.
paper_title: Chemical ant colony algorithm with supramolecular coefficient and multivariate calibration to calix[n]arenas(n = 4, 6, 8) supramolecular system
